You are buying on a very nice Bushmaster AR-15! Many prefer this over Colt or other higher priced AR's.  This was prior to moving operations to New York - and prior to Walmart beating the quality down.

This is not the newer, cheaper $750 Walmart Bushmaster or the carbon/carbine version that others are trying to sell you for $1500. This is the sought after and more desirable weapon back when they built them tight and heavier in Windham, ME. If you are not familiar, do some research and you will quickly gain an appreciation for this weapon and why they are desirable! (Read "HISTORY" below).
It also reads 5.56mm-.223 on the lower, indicating you can shoot 5.56mm rounds out of this gun, unlike some of the newer uppers.

Bushmaster production continued in Windham, Maine until March of 2011 when it was moved to Ilion, New York, to consolidate operations with other Freedom Group manufacturing. The facility in Windham was closed and the employees were laid off. (Source: http://www.grampasgunreviews.com/WindhamWeaponryMPC)

MARKINGS: "B.F.I.  - Windham, ME, - U.S.A." = Bushmaster Firearms International.

ACTION: Very smooth and crisp action. This was not test fired, however we did fire it with a snap cap and the trigger feels good and sounds like the hammer hit the snap cap appropriately.

title: For Sale:  Colt 6920 HB Heavy Barrel 1 of 300 made
postcontent: This is an extremely rare New In Box (NIB) Colt LE 6920HB. This gun is 100% new, unfired with correct factory matching serial numbered box. All is just as when shipped from Colt.Firearm purchased it directly from (SA) Specialized Armament. The rifle comes with the factory accessory pack with (2) 20 round magazines and all accessories from Colt in their unopened packages. This rifle also has the sought after Restricted LE Roll Marks. This Colt rifle is for the discriminating Colt collector or shooter. It's the “HB” that makes this rifle so very rare. "M4 heavy Barrel" based on the 14.5 inch SOCOM M4A1 barrel (R0921HB). The history on the special run of these Colt rifles: With the assault weapons ban over, Ken Elmore, owner of SA, was able to approach Colt with the idea of authenticating each of these rifles. Colt approved. For Colt to produce a "Special Production" weapon they require a minimum order of 300 units. This 6920HB is 1 of only 134 HB's that were ever made available for civilian purchase. There were 300 total HB’s made by Colt exclusively for SA for law enforcement however 134 of them were made available to civilians when the assault weapon ban expired in 2004. The LE 6920 HB is one of the most desirable Colt AR-15 type rifles ever produced. It has a full heavy barrel (no narrowing under the hand guards like the standard 6920) with cut outs for mounting a M203. As mentioned, this weapon is new/unfired and in the factory box with all accessories. There are not many collectors who know these Colt Special Production weapons exist and very few will ever have the opportunity to own a 6920 HB. You can also call Colt's 800 number and get verification from their customer service line that it is a FACTORY PRODUCED LE 6920HB.The Colt factory has ALL 300 Special Production AR-15's cataloged separately, which makes it a very collectible rifle.

title: For Sale:  NIB Colt LE 6920 SOCOM M4A1 AR-15 Quad Rail AR15
postcontent:
New Colt M4 6920 in orginal box and plastic. Just purchased three months ago, never fired, kept in the box and plastic. This is the Colt with the flip up sight in the rear and heavy mil-spec barrel. It also has the upgraded stock. Includes 2 30-round Colt Magazines, cleaning kit, rail covers and manual in unopened accessory kit.

Colt M4 AR 15 new in box, unopened accesory pack, original box and plastic, never fired.
16.1" M4 "medium-Heavy contour" barrel, with a chrome-lined bore and chamber and M4 feed ramp, as developed for military and law enforcement. Note: This is not the lighter barrel Colt uses on the LE6940 and other less expensive LE models. (The difference is most obvious when you look underneath the quad rails, or handguards, of each model. Although outwardly similar in photos, you will notice the less-expensive LE6940 has a thin, "pencil-barrel" contour hidden under proprietary rails! Not so with the SOCOM.. This beast is built like a sledgehammer, from one end to the other.)
M4 Match Grade Barrel is rifled with 1:7" twist. This distinguishes it from most other AR-15 brands on the market, as most are rifled 1:9" and can't stabilize longer, heavier, barrier-penetrating projectiles like the Colt M4 barrel.
Magnetic Particle Inspected Barrel and Bolt, with "MP" certification markings. These parts are Mil-Spec and manufactured to withstand the intense heat and pressure of even suppressed, full-auto fire.
Factory-installed Knight's Armament M4 Carbine RAS picatinny MIL-STD-1913 quad rail system, including the optional, locking rail cover panels. These very solid rails are ideal for quickly mounting any combination of flashlight, laser, front pistol grip, bipod or other accessories.
2 new metal Colt 30-round magazines
Matech BUIS (metal). This high quality, flip-up, adjustable, Back-Up Iron Sight features instant clickable, graduated elevation settings out to 600 meters. Not available on most flip-up sights.
Genuine M-16 type "full auto" bolt carrier group. Mil-Spec. This is not the structurally weaker, reduced bolt carrier found in some lesser brands of civilian AR-15 rifles.
Flat-Top, Mil-Spec Upper Receiver (not proprietary upper receiver dimensions, as offered on the LE6940 flat top.) Optics/Night-vision ready. (E.g., Although not included with this NIB Colt, an EOTech XPS3 would be an all-around superb choice for co-witnessing with the iron sights, and night-vision compatible.)
Ambidextrous safe/fire selector switch. Again, not found on most other AR-15 rifles.
Front and rear sling swivels. (G.I. Mil-Spec sling is also included in the accessory pouch.)
Bayonet Lug
H2 Buffer (dual tungstens, single steel) for reduced recoil and lightning fast follow-up shots
Mil-Spec "A2" features, including birdcage flash hider, adjustable pinned front sight and rear pistol grip
A Colt exclusive: Lower receiver is roll marked "M4A1 Carbine" directly under the Colt logos. A nod to its military heritage. Many AR-15 fans love this very unique lower receiver (and yes, I'm one of them.)
.223/5.56 caliber
Colt rail covers
Caliber-specific roll markings are also distinctly absent from the receiver of this SOCOM edition. (5.56 NATO only appears on the muzzle end of the M4 barrel). (Apparently the absence of the 5.56 NATO marking made it technically legal for export to certain locations that restrict NATO caliber weapons; so a number of these already rare, limited edition Colts are leaving the U.S. market.)
The photos below are of the actual rifle for sale. This is truly a top-of-the-line semi-automatic Colt AR15 carbine. Until just these last few years, there were no new production, genuine Colt AR rifles available to the general public (not since the 80's!) Beginning in 2009, as U.S. miltary M4 orders were expected to decline, a small quantity of genuine Colt M4A1 ARs started trickling into the civilian market. Since then, the demand has steadily increased and this limited edition SOCOM carbine represents the best of the latest Colt production. It weighs 7 lbs and is 32" long with the buttstock in the collapsed position. It is equipped with a civilian-legal 16.1" version of the M4 barrel, with its 1:7" twist (RH 6-groove.) -- ideal for stabilizing a greater variety of 5.56x45mm NATO (and .223 Remington) loads, for superb accuracy. It is unfired, new in box, and includes the factory accessories and manual. The sealed pouch contains two Colt brand 30-round aluminum magazines (green follower), the Colt Safety and Instruction Manual, 4 Knight's Armament polymer quad rail covers (black) with metal locking tabs, Mil-Spec two-point sling (black), one bronze chamber brush, one bronze bore brush, and a segmented cleaning rod.

Although this configuration is descended from the military carbines used by elite forces under Special Operations Command (SOCOM), even sharing many of the same Mil-Spec parts, this Colt is generally civilian legal, at least for now, in the "free" states (not CA, NY, and some other states.) Before you bid, it is your responsibility to know your state and local laws regarding new production AR-15 semi-automatic rifles and detachable 30-round magazines. If you have questions, please don't wait until the last day. I will do my best to answer any questions you have about the auction.

Rifle is ready for immediate shipment to the winning bidder's FFL, upon receipt of full payment and a signed copy of the receiving FFL. I will accept discreet Paypal (add 3% to cover their fees). Insured UPS shipping is $55 to any legal location in the lower 48 states. Rifle, magazines and accessories will be packed correctly, and double-boxed before shipment to your FFL.

title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson M&P 9mm Full Size, package deal with LOTS of add-ons and mags!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
postcontent:
I purchased this M&P last year In May of 2012. Still have all original paperwork and factory casing. It's sat in my safe the entire time and has a grand total of 3 trips to the range with only about 200 rounds through it. (frame has 200 rounds, barrel only has 98 through it). The trigger is fantastic with a great reset, and with all the modifications it is WAY more accurate than I am. I'm asking $1100, which is less than the total cost that I paid for everything at pre-panic prices.

***I'm not interested in any trades BUT I am looking for a Gen 4 Glock 19 - which I would accept as trade along with cash to make up the difference. (trade must be in similar/like condition as this one)***

I've made the following upgrades:

Barrel:
- Storm Lake threaded barrel w/ thread protector (only has 98 rounds on it). It's wicked accurate and took me forever to finally find one. 1/2x28 thread. I've also got a spare thread protector which is the factory M&P barrel thread protector. that I'll throw it.

Trigger work:
- Apex Tactical DCAEK
- Apex Tactical RAM
- Apex Tactical AEK trigger

The trigger is incredibly smooth, with a solidly clean break, no slop, and no creep and the perfect amount of travel. It is a mountainous improvement over the spongy stock trigger which to be frank, was terrible. The RAM kit provides a really nice tactile reset, which makes for extremely rapid follow-up shots. This trigger setup is phenomenal.

Upgraded extractor:
- Apex Tactical Failure Resistant Extractor. (the stock extractor is an MIM part so I upgraded to something tougher and reliable. It's got a larger surface area and practically eliminates any chances of FTE's.)

Night Sights:
- Truglo TFO's (dots green front, green back - w/ Trijicon tritium for night and fiber optics for low/day light) GREAT sights and VERY bright. These are brand new, purchased as of 1 month ago; so you still have 10 years to go on the tritium.

Magazines:
- 5 factory S&W 17 round magazines w/ 10-8 Performance base plates. I ditched the flimsy plastic base-plates and replaced them with quality 10-8 Performance machined base-plates, they've got cut-outs that make mag transitions very natural and quick, an improvement over the stock base-plates which can make mag rapid mag changes a little goofy because they are so rounded. They've also got dimples drilled into them which makes for an easy place to mark your mags for identification.

I've also had it stippled to enhance the grip; it's a GREAT addition as the stock M&P's are too smooth and feel like holding a bar of soap (to me anyways). The stippling is tastefully done and is aesthetically pleasing. I do not have the small or large backstraps. The backstrap that I use is the medium size and it fits my hand like a glove. You can purchase other backstraps for about $2.50 online anywhere. I do not have the factory box - threw it out since it's junk anyways. I DO have all the original paperwork and factory casing however.

This is a great handgun, and with the trigger work and barrel it's made for a rock-solid performer and it's accuracy exceeds my own pistol-shooting ability. It's an absolute blast to shoot and has functioned FLAWLESSLY on a wide variety of ammo - I avoid steel cased ammo, but I like to know my guns will eat anything (I hate picky guns)...so just to test for function I put a magazine worth of steel-cased ammo through and it went through it without a hitch, every round has otherwise been brass-cased from a variety of manufacturers and has functioned without a single problem.

I take extremely good care of my firearms, and for all intents and purposes this is a like-new pistol. No scratches, dings, wear etc. and the melonite coating looks fantastic. The ONLY reason that I am selling this is to pick up a Glock for concealed carry and to fund another project.


Here's the cost breakdown:

- Firearm (purchased 5/12) $550
- Barrel (purchased from MidwayUSA.com): $190
- Truglo TFO's: $90
- Apex DCAEK $97
- Apex RAM $25
- Apex AEK trigger $75
- 17rd. Magazines $40 x 3 = $120 (came with 2, these are the additional 3 I purchased)
- 10-8 base plates x5 @ 20 each $100
- Various s/h costs $50

Total: ~ $1300

Your price: $1100. (or traded for a Gen 4 Glock G19 + $400 cash)

I STRONGLY prefer to sell to a CHL holder. Be willing to sign a bill of sell and present your CHL. If you do not have a CHL I prefer we make the transaction through an FFL and I'll cover the cost.

Call or text Ryan @ REDACTED. Thanks gents!
